import itertools
N,M=map(int,raw_input().split())
data=[map(float,raw_input().split()) for i in range(N)]
maxV=0.0
for comb in itertools.combinations(range(N),M):
    dist=0.0
    for i in range(M-1):
        for j in range(i+1,M):
            t=comb[i]
            s=comb[j]
            dist+=pow(data[t][0]-data[s][0],2)+pow(data[t][1]-data[s][1],2)+pow\
(data[t][2]-data[s][2],2)
    maxV=max(maxV,dist)
print maxV
